cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MED, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper deals with the problem of estimating the 3D pose of a fetus in ultrasound images, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on medical imaging and analysis, which suggests cs.MED (Medical Imaging) as another likely category. The proposed method also involves self-supervised learning and gradient check-pointing, which are ML techniques, indicating cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with anatomical structures and segmentation, which suggests cs.GR (Graphics) as a less likely but still possible category.
